<div class = 'img'><a href = 'http://martinfowler.com/articles/enterpriseREST.html#bounded-contexts'><img src = 'http://martinfowler.com/articles/enterpriseREST/images/brandon-byars.jpg ' width = '100' height = '' alt = '' title = ''/></a></div><p>A common mistake in service-oriented architectures is to let a single service own all of the data about widely used entities, such as products or customers. In his latest installment of <a href="http://martinfowler.com/articles/enterpriseREST.html">enterprise REST</a> <a href="http://twitter.com/BrandonByars">Brandon Byars</a> explains why this is an error and shows how to use the DDD notion of bounded contexts for a better approach.</p>
